HEADWORD: Still-hunt
<hw>Still"-hunt`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A hunting for
game in a quiet and cautious manner, or under cover; stalking; hence,
colloquially, the pursuit of any object quietly and cautiously.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Still"-hunt`er</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Still"-hunt`ing</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
<mark>[U.S.]</mark></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stillicide</ent>⟦br⟧
